Personally, I would use dropwizard.  Spark&#x27;s key point seems to be avoiding annotation based constructs.<p>Compare (Spark):<p><pre><code>  public class HelloWorld {
     public static void main(String[] args) {      
        get(new Route(&quot;/hello&quot;) {
           @Override
           public Object handle(Request request, Response response) {
              return &quot;Hello World!&quot;;
           }
        });
     }
  } 
</code></pre>
to (JAX-RS, which dropwizard uses)<p><pre><code>  @Path(&quot;/hello&quot;)
  public class HelloWorld {
    @GET
    public String get() {
      return &quot;Hello World&quot;;
    }
  }</code></pre>
